caption: Probably the best Vietnamese Pho I have had. I have eaten Pho in pretty much every city I have visited, and this one was AMAZING! The broth was so on point. Definitely eating from here again.
Chinese food, mmm, super yummy. I love this place, excellent food & service. Next time I'll be back with my relatives. Bring your hunger - portions are generous.
Really good, super friendly employees, clean restaurant.
Great little coffee shop. Food is above average. Service is good. Prices, reasonable.

I ordered chicken fried rice and wings. When I walked & arrived at home (should have looked before) and open the bag, I smelled a burnt smell. I opened the chicken fried rice and it was burnt.  I called to express my frustration and the guy wouldn't even let me finish my sentence before talking over me to say "well do you want your money back or to make a new one". When I ordered a new one (because the rice is generally good) I walked in and shared that it was an inconvenience. Instead of apologizing, He decided to ARGUE with me and said "You are the only one who complain". He said everyone else wants me to make it "well done". This was NOT well done, it was burnt and this was MY food - not everyone else's. I am most disappointed that he decided to ARGUE with me about my order. I was a regular but now I am no longer going to use their services. There should have been a thank you for using our services especially during a pandemic but instead there was a slammed door in my face. Very disrespectful and unacceptable. Make sure you check your food before you leave!
This is a Vietnamese restaurant pretending to be pan-asian   The Chinese food is just awful.

Excellent food and excellent service! I stopped in here for a quick lunch. I am vegetarian and happily, I noticed that they have quite a few vegetarian options. I spoke with the gentleman behind the counter and clarified what was in the sauce.   He was very nice, and I ended up having tofu with tomato peppers and onions and the sauce was absolutely delicious! I ate there, there are some nice padded bar stools facing out onto the street. I will definitely be back! :)
Friendly, cozy, delicious hot food
This spot offers superb service and delightful food. My favourite place in town. The drinks and food came out rapidly and the prices are affordable. Will definitely recommend this place.
I had to move to other city, I really really miss this amazing food, the most missing is the fried rice ❤️ 🍛 highly recommended to the rice lovers!

It's literally been an hour and a half since we ordered take out and it's not done. The estimated time was twenty minutes. This is the only negative review I've left for a restaurant ever. This is just nonsense.  Update: it was missing part of the order. They wanted to offer me a credit for next time. Ha!
My to go place for weekday last minute meals. Totally recommend the chicken vegetable soup and the beef and broccoli!
Extremely delicious. The service could be better, but I guess nothing is perfect
Great food!! Definitely will be back.

I love Far East Kitchen! The food is really good, especially the kung pao chicken and vegetable fried rice. The fastest way to get your food is to call in your order and then come pick it up yourself. Delivery can take way too long, so you should avoid it if you can. Lots of other reviews have mentioned long wait times regardless, which is completely true, but these folks work out of a really small kitchen, so try to be patient and understand they can only fulfill so many orders at a time. In my experience, the food is always worth the wait. Also, if you pay with a debit card, remember to bring some cash for a tip!

This place needs to be shut down. I ordered beef with broccoli. The meat tasted weird, it was not fresh and barely cooked. I was hungry and at first i didnt notice it but after having a few bites i vomited. The smell was disgusting. I was a regular customer for over a year this never happened to me before. When i called them they said they were on a vacation for a week and the meat was in the fridge....
Food is really good. Long wait times. I recommend ordering online or by phone and then going to pick up your food. Deliveries are also a very long wait.
Love love love
Food is good but always have to wait a little too long to get your food.

This is my first time ordering here I ordered chicken Pad Thai beef and broccoli and sweet and sour chicken there was not enough sauce on any of our entrees. Very  light flavor. The meat was cooked well. But We felt like it could have been better in larger  containers to allow for extra sauce. Ijs what are we supposed to put on the white rice?

My daughter and I tried it for the first time tonight. We got beef chow mein and chicken pad Thai. Also egg rolls. It took a little while longer than it was supposed to have. However it was Chinese New year so somewhat understandable. Really liked it. We thought it was the best Chinese food we've had in RP (been here about 9 years.)
Some of the best Chinese and Vietnamese food in the Chicago area!
Food is Amazing
Well made sauces, quality ingredients.

Great small family owned business and friendly staff! Food is very tasty and full of flavor. I had a great experience with the kind staff. General Tso's Chicken and the Beef Pho is a must have! Lemon grass chicken is also my usual go to.

Great food and amazing service! The owners are absolutely fabulous and very sweet— they went above and beyond to help correct an honest mistake they made in preparing my pickup order.  They’ve made me a loyal customer for many years.

We have ordered from this place a few times, but we won't be going back. This last time, the food was about 45 minutes late (about 2 hours after we ordered it via EatStreet) and repeated calls to the restaurant were going unanswered. We were just about to give up when they showed up. No apology or anything.  To make matters worse, last night we were reheating up the leftovers and THERE WAS A PIECE OF METAL IN THE LEMONGRASS CHICKEN. As I ate a forkful of food, I felt something hard and sharp in my mouth. When I pulled it out, it was a long, thin piece of metal. Disgusting and horrible food practices.  I would recommend you avoid this place at all costs.
Very tasty food.
Fast service

Been here twice. Once for food and again for smoothies. The fried rice, sesame chicken and crab Rangoons were all excellent. I wasn't a huge fan of the egg rolls, but it's because they're just done differently than I'm used to.  The Avacado smoothie!!! It's delicious and super affordable for Chicago, try that one for sure 😁

I ordered based on all the good reviews but was highly disappointed. I order the sweet and sour chicken, crab Rangoon, pad Thai, and some chicken teriyaki sticks. First off, the chicken teriyaki sticks were green and slimy. Unedible and disgusting. The pad Thai had no sauce or flavor whatsoever and the tofu was really mushy. The sweet and sour chicken was covered in a thick breading shell and the pieces of chicken inside were not fully cooked. The crab Rangoon was OK but definitely not memorable.  Over all really dissatisfied, I haven’t had food this bad in a long time. Maybe it was an off night, but I definitely won’t be ordering food from this restaurant again.

Customer service was nice and friendly, but the food wasn’t that great.  I got the orange chicken and there wasn’t much or any sauce and barely the orange flavor.  I also got vegetable fried rice which was also dry and didn’t compare to other fried rice’s I’ve had.  Maybe I ordered the wrong things compared to the other reviews...

Called this place at lunch time on a Tuesday. No-one picked up my calls. I decide to drive there because I was pretty close. I walked in to place my order and was told he couldn't take my order right now and to come back later. I will never patronize here if this was my first experience. This is a critique of the service, not the food.
This food is the best don’t listen to the bad reviews.Keep up the good food. #food4life
Always yummy :)
1st timer and very satisfied with my pick up experience.
Love this!!! Egg rolls and the chow mein with lots of vegetable, specially onions that I love, is sooo good!!!

My favorite place for takeout. Good food. Great flavors. Veggies are colorful and crisp. Sauces are lovely and well-balanced. Crab Rangoon is one of my favorite splurges. Vegetable fried rice has large veggies in it!! Best chinese takeout near Morse Red Line stop. Run by a fabulous family. Highly recommend.
Great asian cuisine with a focus on Vietnamese. Recommend the Bahn Mi and the bubble tea.
I eat here all the time. Friendly employees, good food, consistent-- a great little restaurant!! Good selection too, especially if you feel like Vietnamese!
Friendly staff and great food. I really am a fan of their sandwiches.
My favorite go-to restaurant. Lots of big veggies, and not too thick and saucy. Yum yum!!

The entree was 100% wrong. The egg rolls had been over fried, to the point i was almost unable to consume them. Even the hot sauce was jacked. It was just red pepper flakes, with some kind of oil introduced. If i didnt have a 102 temp, i would have walked all the way back and asked for a refund. Super disappointing! I would NEVER eat here again and im not one to complain.
A cozy restaurant. the restaurant being small has its perks- great place for people who wants to eat alone.  And the food is amazing.
I love the Jumbo shrimp fried rice and he was nice enough to make it spicy for me. Will come back again to try the Vietnamese dishes.
Great food, China Town quality.
Good food prepared fresh
I loved their food and it has a lot of flavors
Owner is a really nice guy. Takes good care of the customers. Had the seafood pho, and it was delicious.

Dont let any bad reviews get to you. This place is great. I don't normally review restaurants but I felt this place definitely deserved at least a 4. The food is definitely good consistently. I live right around the block and this has become one of my new favorite places. Personally I love the Banh Mi/Summer Roll but the pho is fantastic as well.

By the way,  Kira, don't use Grubhub and you might not have the problems that you had. I have lived in both Seattle and San Francisco and both have incredible Chinese food. Some of the restaurants are world famous there. I didn't give this place a 5 star rating, but 4 stars are pretty dog-gone good, and for the vegetables I will give it 5 stars. This is NOT mediocre food everybody, not at all: Kira is wrong here on that. Kira, I really suggest trying them again. It's actually quite delicious food. I was needing some mixed vegetables and chicken and they cooked up a really nice dish for me with all of my favorite vegetables. That was a really nice dish. It's a different flavor because it has a little bit of smoked flavor to it. That was a surprise; and it first I thought I wouldn't like it, but it was actually really good. The very fresh vegetables almost had a roasted taste to them. That might explain the smoked flavor. Thank God they were not overcooked at all. They are really crunchy and tasty. Yum ! I also ordered a hot and sour soup which turned out to be very good as well but it had a surprise too: it was a little bit sweet. This is a very good choice for a different restaurant when you have gone to your favorite chinese restaurant one too many times and have taste bud burnout. And I was feeling pretty bad before I ate. This is healthy food because I'm feeling a lot better...a lot better. I will go back again, and I'm a picky eater. Also it's a very good value for the price. One more thing, now that I have finished dinner: I have to say that this is my new favorite restaurant in the neighborhood. I'm thrilled. This out did my other favorite restaurant, especially for the vegetables. Congratulations!
This Is my go to place when I don't want to cook. The people are nice and you a ton of food. I always have enough for lunch the nest day.
This place is great. The General Tso's Chicken is amazing.

I used Grubhub and my order was delivered wrong. When I asked the driver about it, he had already rushed into his car and told me it was right, then quickly drove away. I called the restaurant, and they said they'd send the driver back with the correct item. More than an hour later, I still hadn't heard back from anyone. When I called back, I was told they hadn't seen the driver since I called the first time. The man I spoke to kept making excuses and never made any kind of offer to rectify the situation. On top of that, the food is mediocre, at best. I will not be ordering from here in the future.

The staff was very friendly! The food was good, the menu extensive. The Pho is recommended. Egg rolls could be a little better, but they were pretty good anyway. Fresh ingredients and NO MSG food. I like having a great Chinese / Vietnamese option within walking distance.
